## Setup Instructions

### 1. Add GitHub Secrets

Go to your repo â†’ âš™ï¸ Settings â†’ **Secrets and variables â†’ Actions** â†’ **New repository secret**, and add:

| Secret Name  | Value                             |
| ------------ | --------------------------------- |
| `EMAIL_USER` | Your Gmail address                |
| `EMAIL_PASS` | App password (not your real pass) |
| `EMAIL_TO`   | Recipient email address           |

> ğŸ’¡ **Use an App Password** from your Gmail settings (Google > Security > App passwords).

---

### 2. Install Dependencies (locally or in CI)

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

### â†» 3. Schedule the Workflow (already set up)

Your GitHub Action (`send_news.yml`) runs **every day at 07:30 UTC**. You can also run it manually from the GitHub Actions tab.

